transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, this is Ed Vegas calling from Rochelle, Indiana. I just received through the mail a refill and I did not order it.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me help you out. Can I have your phone number so I can pull up your account?

Speaker 2: Yes, seven six five four three eight. Oh—

Speaker 1: Seven seven five.

Speaker 2: Thank you, Ed, can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 1: One eight fifty.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much. I see your VIP status.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay. I see the doctor put you on monthly refills, which you do not have to have.

Speaker 2: And how's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 1: It's hitting, this is it, you know.

Speaker 2: It's okay. Do you happen to have the pills on you right now?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Can you take out an individual pill and tell me what's on it?

Speaker 1: Why is the bank calling me?

Speaker 2: Is the bank calling? Well, it's um—

Speaker 1: Is there AC on there?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay. Yeah, that's what I thought. Okay. Those are just regular generic Viagra. Those are not the AGV.

Speaker 2: Pharmacy. Well, you know what, I called when I first received those.

Speaker 1: I did not think I got the right—and she has said, is it rectangle or round?

Speaker 2: And it is rectangular.

Speaker 1: Yeah, she said that was the AGV.

Speaker 2: I wish there— I wish she left notes here because I would have told her no, you're completely wrong.

Speaker 1: No, those are not. No, those are just regular generic. Give me a second.

Speaker 2: I'm gonna get you out a replacement and then I'm going to tell you how you can confirm it's the correct medication.

Speaker 1: Give me one second. Okay.

Speaker 2: Sometimes the pharmacy runs out of AGV and then they send generics, which creates—but they don't tell us and that creates a bunch—

Speaker 1: Problems, so I've had the generics before and that's why I tried to get exactly the AGV.

Speaker 2: Exactly, and then I didn't think that I got it, but they assured me if it was triangle shape, that was AGV.

Speaker 1: So, yeah, no, it says AC and the bottle says APCO.

Speaker 2: Okay. Okay, perfect.

Speaker 1: All right, Ed. So when you get this new bottle in the mail, this is how you're going to confirm.

Speaker 2: It's the AGV on the bottle. It's going to say AGV.

Speaker 1: But it's also going to say Greenstone and—

Speaker 2: Greenstone is the name of Pfizer's—

Speaker 1: Manufacturer in France, and then on the pills the only number imprinted is going to be the number 100 for the milligrams.

Speaker 2: And those are the two ways you can confirm because your bottle now says APCO—

Speaker 1: Which is the manufacturer from us and yeah, and they say AC, so just go ahead and throw those out.

Speaker 2: I'm sending you a quantity of 30 of them to make up for your—

Speaker 1: Your initial order and your refill, and then what I'm going to do—

Speaker 2: I'm going to go ahead and pause your refills for six months.

Speaker 1: I'm going to pause it till July 31st of 2026.

Speaker 2: Because if I cancel now it will delete your profile and the pharmacy would not be able to send you out that replacement.

Speaker 1: And I'll give you my extension so you can call me back and let me know how the AGV works out.

Speaker 2: You have a pen?

Speaker 1: I'm getting one. Okay. Okay, go ahead. Okay, it's zero zero here.

Speaker 2: I'm going to give you a number because you called through the pharmacy. Okay, so it's yeah. Yeah, 1-800—

Speaker 1: Okay, seven five.

Speaker 2: Nine eight zero seven.

Speaker 1: And my extension is zero zero two zero.

Speaker 2: And my name is Michelle.

Speaker 1: Okay, Michelle.

Speaker 2: Cool. Well, that's great. I think yeah, I appreciate this. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, of course.

Speaker 2: I'm sorry, whoever you talked to, but now you have my extension and then you won't have to sit on hold either.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: That's great. Well, I'll look forward to that then. Super awesome.

Speaker 1: Yeah, they'll be shipping out tomorrow morning.

Speaker 2: They'll email you a tracking number, but you'll get it in five days or less.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you Michelle.

Speaker 2: No problem, glad I could help. Have a great evening.

Speaker 1: Thanks so much.
